results.title: Third-Alarm Apartment Building Fire

-M_VlW6-gBLnBnCL5ntH.text: Incident reported at 1314 Irving Ave N.

-M_VlWQCw5Z2ZBhvqQvs.text: Firefighters have received a report that a building is on fire.

-M_VleqgeS6Gy9hHKVWy.text: According to firefighters, a couch is reportedly on fire on a balcony.

-M_W-WBl7B91AW5Tg27z.text: Firefighters confirm they have cleared the fire on the roof.

-M_W00l1rMtIC0vFUsGk.text: Firefighters report still seeing some smoke and residual heat from ventilations on the roof.

-M_W4wfFa2eGU7a2UVMI.text: Firefighters confirm that the fire has been fully extinguished.

nib.text:
Firefighters battled a three-alarm fire which broke out in the Near North neighborhood of Minneapolis Wednesday morning.

At approximately 8:30 a.m., firefighters confirmed fire on the third floor of the three-story building on the 1300 block of Irving Avenue North.

Crews put out the fire in the apartment where it started, but the fire had extended into the attic. 

Firefighters raised a second alarm, and then a third, requesting additional personnel.

As of about 9:30 a.m., firefighters reported that the roof was clear of visible fire, but they were still detecting smoke and heat at the ventilations.

At 10 a.m., firefighters confirmed the fire had been fully extinguished.

Residents were evacuated from the building and there have been no reports of injuries.

The fire is under investigation.
